      The name of the system, the heritage check system, gets it's name as such:<br/><br/>Among many individuals, it's not uncommon for a successor to be willed 'their heritage' from the passing of those before them and reinvest it to further benefit from the inheritance. The system is basically a larger scale version of that for the government and the American people. Combined with the monthly check, this gives rise to the Heinlein's name for it, "The Heritage Check System".

                  
    </td>
  </tr>


  <tr id="row_1926" onmouseover="showDiv('CommentBar_1926');" onmouseout="hideDiv('CommentBar_1926')" class="IdeaScale_Comment_Normal">
    <td valign="top" style="padding:3px;">

    <table width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
