      To make a comparison between our current monetary system and the Heinlein Heritage check system would be as such:<br/><br/>On a national scale, the Heinlein Heritage system works similar to this analogy:<br/>"I work an hour, and am paid. I invest any extra I have (instead of just letting it sit around) so the interest can supplement my normal income." As time goes it, financial shape steadily improves, and people reap the benefit of their labors. And the investment fuels others to do more work to make a healthier economy overall.<br/><br/>Our current system works more according to this analogy:<br/>"I work an hour, for my efforts, instead of being paid, I am given a credit card with a certain limit (which still has to be paid back). Any extra I have, I burn for fear someone else may benefit from it more than I." As time goes, our analogy person has to work harder and harder to pay off more and more debt only by using more debt, and get less out of their work with each pass, and there is much wasted resources.

                  
    </td>
  </tr>


  <tr id="row_1930" onmouseover="showDiv('CommentBar_1930');" onmouseout="hideDiv('CommentBar_1930')" class="IdeaScale_Comment_Normal">
