      As an addendum, one idea that Heinlein suggested (although I think would have to be further researched before being implemented) is that to create more balance, any un-bought product at the end of a business cycle (with the excess funds based on their production), would be bought up at specifically production price to save companies from negatives of creating too much product. These are then used by the government as the government sees fit, and ensures that prices are kept low because supply would be high.

                  
    </td>
  </tr>


  <tr id="row_1931" onmouseover="showDiv('CommentBar_1931');" onmouseout="hideDiv('CommentBar_1931')" class="IdeaScale_Comment_Normal">
